    • Constructor Detail

      • LoggedOnStatusEvent

        public LoggedOnStatusEvent(Object source,
                           int logonEventType,
                           IFIXMessage fixMessage,
                           boolean externalRequest,
                           boolean loggedOn,
                           IConnectionPoint connectionPoint,
                           Connection connection,
                           String textMessage)
        Logged on status change event.
        Parameters:
        source - source
        logonEventType - Indicates the type of log on status change. See LoggedOnStatusEvent for the valid logon event types.
        fixMessage - FIX message associated with this event, if any. ie Logon or logout message.
        externalRequest - True if the logon/out originated externally.
        loggedOn - True if session is logged on following this event.
        connectionPoint - Connection point associated with the session at the time of this event.
        connection - Connection associated with the session at the time of this event.
        textMessage - Text message associated with this event - for example a log out reason.
